    "actor_description": "Love is still there, embarrassingly alive, and that\u2019s what makes it hurt. My mind keeps snapping back to them like a tongue to a broken tooth\u2014testing the gap, flinching, returning anyway. My chest feels hollow and hot at once, and the future suddenly looks thinner, like it lost a room I was counting on. I can\u2019t quite stop reaching, even if it\u2019s only with my attention.",
    "description_text": "{actor} looks caught on something they can't set down\u2014their gaze lingering, attention looping back, breath coming a little shallow. Their expression carries a tender ache that doesn\u2019t harden into anger, more like a quiet wound staying open while they try to stand upright.",
